# Express

- Layered: routes → controllers → services → data. Keep HTTP out of services.
- Async handlers must forward rejections to a central error middleware.
- One error middleware last; consistent JSON `{ error: { code, message } }`.
- Validate params/query/body with a schema (Zod/Joi) at the boundary.
- Default security: helmet, explicit CORS allowlist, rate limiting, body limits.
- Validated env config; fail fast on missing vars. Never log secrets/tokens.
